President Joe Biden delivered a speech at Union Trust in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, where he highlighted the importance of the upcoming elections and the need to maintain control of the Senate and House of Representatives. He expressed concern about the current state of the Republican Party, stating that the MAGA Republicans have a different view of government and institutions. Biden emphasized the potential consequences if Republicans gain control, such as their desire to undo Social Security and Medicare, increase drug prices, and roll back environmental regulations. He also discussed his administration's accomplishments, including job creation, investment in research and development, and efforts to lower prescription drug costs. Biden called for support for John Fetterman in the upcoming election and stressed the importance of winning to protect the progress made in the country. He discussed the significance of American democracy on a global scale and urged everyone to vote and get others to vote.